            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The school charges very high fees, and what is more concerning is the arbitrary increase in fees every year. Instead of a reasonable annual hike (upto 10% as many schools are doing), the fee structure is changed as per their convenience, even for existing students. This creates a financial burden and lack of transparency for parents.\n\nThe facilities and overall quality do not justify such high and frequently changing fees. Additionally, the way parents are treated by the management is not professional. Communication lacks respect and clarity.\n\nIn particular, the behavior of the Principal, Mrs. Aruna, is not approachable or courteous, which is disappointing.\n\nOverall, the school needs to improve transparency in fee structure, upgrade facilities, and maintain respectful communication with parents.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
